hello my name is Faisal Khan I'm

Cloud I.T
so soon after I started Ecom dot in
which is a cloud native company on AWS I
started seeking out groups and
communities to learn more about AWS and
this is where I came across the AWS
Hyderabad User Group
and then I realized that I have a lot
more to offer to the group so I started
conducting a lot more meetups speaking
at different sessions
and this led on to further developing a
lot more things for the community and on
that same line I went on to build a
global discussion forum called let's
talk AWS
recently I received a call from one of
my trainees in the U.S and he was elated
to let me know that he actually got into
AWS after completing my training on
Solutions architecture
with all of the work that I did for the
community in terms of speaking events or
building out tools for the community the
rewards were great and one of those
rewards was actually becoming the user
group leader for the AWS Hyderabad user
group and on that same line a few months
later I also happened to be selected for
the AWS Community Builder program and
with consistent efforts and a lot more
work soon I became an AWS hero
my advice to anyone who's building out
within the AWS Community is to not be
afraid of making your own path and try
not to follow Trends try to specialize
in areas that you feel interested in
because expertise in certain areas will
always Outlast trends
